Install Standard Data Bundles Powered by Data Kits

After you create your Data Cloud instance and set up your Salesforce CRM connection, you can install standard data bundles that are powered by data kits to deploy data within Data Cloud.

NOTE In Standard Data Bundles, the data kits that back the standard data bundles are available based on your current licensing and products you use within Salesforce. The data kits that power the Service Cloud and Sales Cloud are available if you’ve set up your Salesforce CRM.
NOTE The Installed Version is the version currently installed. The Latest Version is the most current version of the standard data bundle.
In Data Cloud, select  then Data Cloud Setup.
Select Salesforce CRM.
In the list of Standard Data Bundles, click  for the desired bundle, and select Install.
In the Package Install flow, follow the standard process for installing a data kit.

To uninstall a standard data bundle, click  for the desired bundle, and select Uninstall. Then, follow the standard uninstall process for a data kit.
